  "content": "sts**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel chunking_pipeline`\nExpected: All existing + 4 new tests pass.\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat(m3.4): add discover_cross_file_relations for declaration→usage tracking (D74)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: End-to-end validation — re-run benchmark\n\n**Files:**\n- No code changes — validation only\n\n**Step 1: Build release binaries**\n\nRun: `cd /root/corvia-project/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo build --release`\nExpected: Compiles successfully.\n\n**Step 2: Re-run the benchmark**\n\nRun: `./scripts/benchmark.sh`\nExpected: Full pipeline completes — inference, init, ingest, serve, 8 queries, summary.\n\n**Step 3: Compare edge counts**\n\nRun: `cd .benchmark-workspace && ../target/release/corvia graph --scope corvia-benchmark 2>&1 | grep 'edges in scope'`\nExpected: Significantly more than 236 edges (target: 500+).\n\n**Step 4: Compare benchmark results**\n\nRun: `cat benchmark-results/*/summary.json | jq '.queries[] | {id, vector_count: .vector.sources_count, graph_count: .graph.sources_count, graph_expanded: .graph.graph_expanded}'`\nExpected: `graph_expanded` should be 5+ for most queries (was 0-2 before).\n\n**Step 5: Compare source file diversity**\n\nRun:\n```bash\nfor n in 1 2 3 4; do\n  echo \"Query $n:\"\n  echo \"  Vector files: $(cat benchmark-results/*/query-${n}-vector.json | jq '[.sources[].source_file] | unique | length')\"\n  echo \"  Graph files:  $(cat benchmark-results/*/query-${n}-graph.json | jq '[.sources[].source_file] | unique | length')\"\ndone\n```\nExpected: Graph-expanded results should include more unique source files than vector-only.\n\n**Step 6: Commit the results (if significant improvement)**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"chore(m3.4): benchmark validation — graph edge improvements verified\"\n```\n\n---\n\n\n### Task 6: Add `.fastembed_cache/` to `.gitignore`\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `.gitignore`\n\n**Step 1: Append to `.gitignore`**\n\nAdd:\n```",
